  "texts": [
    "In addition to finding support for their hypothesis, they found a positive correlation between the number of internal details participants provided when remembering the past and imagining the future.",
    "These results are consistent with the constructive episodic simulation hypothesis, which suggests that we imagine future experiences by recombining elements from episodic memories (Schacter & Addis, 2007).",
    "Other researchers have similarly adapted the interview to study future thinking.",
    "For example, Race et al. (2011) studied amnesic individuals with the interview, and showed that damage to the medial temporal lobe led to reductions in central episodic details on both episodic memory and future thinking tasks, despite intact descriptive abilities (i.e., normal performance when describing pictures).",
    "Because the interview can be used to study features of autobiographical memory and future thinking, the procedure has seen widespread use across domains of psychology."
  ],
